articles.title: An Australia police officer who shocked a 95-year-old woman with a Taser is guilty of manslaughter - The Associated Press
articles.description: A police officer who shocked a 95-year-old nursing home resident with a Taser was found guilty of manslaughter in an Australian court. A jury found Kristian James Samuel White guilty Wednesday after 20 hours of deliberation. Clare Nowland, a great-grandmother…
